-- Impsa to Invest $116 Million in Brazil Wind Turbine Plant in South
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-02-08T15:32:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/impsa-to-invest-116-million-in-brazil-wind-turbine-plant-in-south.html
Industrias Metalurgicas Pescarmona
SA, an Argentinean wind-turbine maker, plans to build a 200
million-real wind-turbine plant in the Brazilian state of Rio
Grande do Sul, Vice-President Jose Luis Menghini said today in
an interview in  Sao Paulo .  The plant will have capacity to produce 140 machines a year
and will start operating in 2013, according to Menghini.  Impsa also plans to build a 50 million-real electronics
factory for wind farms, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Karen Eeuwens at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net  